Privacy Policy for FAM

Last Updated: 25-2-2025

1. Introduction

Welcome to FAM ("we," "our," or "us"). We are committed to protecting your privacy and personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our FAM mobile application and related services.

2. Information We Collect

2.1 Personal Information:
• Name and username
• Email address
• Profile picture
• Phone number
• Payment information
• Location data (optional)
• Device information

2.2 User Content:
• Digital assets you upload
• Comments and interactions
• Transaction history
• Messages with other users

2.3 Automatically Collected Information:
• Device ID
• IP address
• Usage data
• Access timestamps
• App performance data

3. How We Use Your Information

We use your information to:
• Provide and maintain our services
• Process your transactions
• Communicate with you
• Improve our services
• Detect and prevent fraud
• Comply with legal obligations
• Send notifications about your account
• Provide customer support

4. Information Sharing and Disclosure

We may share your information with:
• Other users (as per your privacy settings)
• Payment processors
• Service providers
• Law enforcement (when legally required)
• Business partners (with your consent)

We do NOT sell your personal information to third parties.

5. Data Security

We implement appropriate security measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction.

6. Your Rights

You have the right to:
• Access your personal information
• Correct inaccurate data
• Delete your account
• Opt-out of marketing communications
• Update your privacy settings
• Export your data

7. Children's Privacy

Our service is not intended for users under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect information from children under 13.

8. Changes to Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. We will notify you of any significant changes through the app or email.

9. Data Storage and Transfer

Your data is stored on secure servers and may be transferred to and processed in countries other than your own.

10. Third-Party Services

Our app may contain links to third-party services. We are not responsible for their privacy practices.

11. Cookies and Tracking

We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to improve user experience and analyze app usage.

12. Marketing Communications

We may send you marketing communications with your consent. You can opt-out at any time.

13. Contact Information

For privacy-related questions or concerns, contact us at:
[Your Contact Email]
[Your Physical Address]

14. Legal Basis for Processing (for EU users)

We process your information based on:
• Contract performance
• Legal obligations
• Legitimate interests
• Your consent

15. Data Retention

We retain your information as long as necessary to provide our services or as required by law.

16. Your California Privacy Rights

California residents have additional rights regarding their personal information under the CCPA.

17. International Users

By using our app, you consent to the transfer of your information to servers in [Your Country] and other locations where we operate.

18. Account Deletion

You can request account deletion through the app settings or by contacting us directly.

19. Data Breaches

We will notify you and relevant authorities of any data breaches as required by law.

20. Effective Date

This Privacy Policy is effective as of 25-2-25.
